Below is a clean set of one-line explanations for every field you mentioned.
You can directly paste these as clarifications to your teams.


---

✅ One-Line Explanations for Each Field

Fuel Tank – Fuel Level Gauge

Fuel Level Gauge: Indicates how much fuel is currently available in the tank (example: 25%, 50%, 75%).


Fuel Tank – Owner

Owner of Fuel Tank: The team responsible for the tank (e.g., Wireline, Wireless, Facilities); if unknown, leave blank.



---

BDFB – Key Fields

Weight Capacity (lbs)

Weight Capacity: The maximum weight the BDFB unit or frame can safely support, measured in pounds; optional if unknown.


Equipment Served

Equipment Served: Identifies which network/service the BDFB powers (e.g., DSL, FIOS, Insider, Data Router, Old Tall, New Tall, Co-Location).


Financial Project ID

Financial Project ID: Internal project or cost-allocation identifier; fill only if the site team tracks it.



---

BDFB Panel – Field Explanations

U-Position

U-Position: The vertical mounting position of the panel inside the rack (e.g., above or below).


Rails Used

Rails Used: Refers to the mounting rails (left/right or both) that support the panel inside the rack.


Orientation

Orientation: The direction the panel faces when installed (typically front-facing).


Order (L → R)

Order (Left to Right): The physical left-to-right sequence of panels inside the BDFB or rack.


Custom Field – BDFB Panel ID

BDFB Panel ID: A wireline-specific identifier for the panel; optional if not used by the site.



---

Battery Fields

Make & Model

already clarified earlier — but if you want a one-liner:

Make & Model: The manufacturer and model number of the battery; DC-Track can import or create the model based on given details.



---

